  "name": "RPlog_Spycraft_-_Part_1",
  "title": "Boots on the Smuggler's Moon",
  "summary": "Aboard the light cruiser Bright Star en route to Nar Shaddaa, the quartermaster Siarra runs a final mission briefing for a Corellian intelligence team, outfitting Druze, Kelnas, and Wrexan in forgettable civilian gear while pilot Tiaryn flies them in. The mission is reconnaissance: locate and assess the most recent shipment of slaves moved by pirates, with strict orders not to start fires, demolish buildings, or provoke a Hutt war. Landing on the city-moon, the team links up with their unremarkable Duros contact Zalla, who slips them through customs and into the back room of the Meltdown Cafe. There, using cover names Mr. Blu, Mr. Red, and Mr. Greene, they learn from Zalla that forty-one captives are already slated for an auction a week out, with viewings beginning the next day. They settle on posing as a buyer (a thirteen-thousand-credit buy-in), pooling their funds, and leveraging Kelnas's old contact Hargsbad, who now runs the relocated club 7th Heaven amid a violent turf war. Zalla agrees to build a buyer legend and deliver the auction data the following night, warning them to stay smart and avoid trouble.",
